### Code Quality ###
Code is not readable yet. Indentation is not consistent in general.

All inconsistent indentation must be fixed to help others reading, editing your code.

Please refer to example below to help you re-indent the code.

## Example

```
body {
  height: 100%;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}

header {
  padding-top: 29px;
  background-color: #786;
  width: 100%;
  text-align: center;
  padding-bottom: 5px;
  margin-bottom: 5px;
}

#map {
  height: 700px;
  width: 100%;
}

p {
  margin-top: 0;
  text-align: center;
}

#inputClass {
  width: 90%;
  margin-bottom: 20px;
  text-indent: inherit;
}

.outputList {
  width: 90%;
  vertical-align: center;
}

a {
  padding-right: 5px;
  padding-left: 5px;
  padding-bottom: 5px;
  padding-top: 5px;
  display: block;
  border: 3px solid #408;
  font-weight: bold;
}

h1 {
  color: #525454;
  font-size: 36px;
  margin: 0 0 10px 0;
  line-height: 40px;
  text-align: center;
}

h2 {
  font-size: 30px;
  line-height: 40px;
}

h3 {
  font-size: 24px;
  line-height: 40px;
  text-align: center;
}

h4 {
  font-size: 18px;
  line-height: 20px;
}

/* Won't be used here */

h5 {
  font-size: 14px;
  line-height: 20px;
}

h6 {
  font-size: 12px;
  line-height: 20px;
}

#pano {
  width: 200px;
  height: 200px;
}
```
